# 14.17 Key Engineering Principles

The project reinforced the following principles:

- Build modular systems.
- Validate incrementally.
- Separate reasoning from execution.
- Standardize environments.
- Design for replacement.
- Treat runtime dependencies as first-class citizens.
- Prefer protocols over custom integrations.
- Focus on architecture before optimization.

These principles guided every major engineering decision.

---

# 14.18 Final Reflection

The Study Abroad Finder began as an exploration of Google ADK and the Model Context Protocol.

It evolved into a comprehensive study of modern AI system design.

Beyond the final application, the project demonstrated how language models, orchestration frameworks, external tools, cloud platforms, and containerized environments can work together to create modular, extensible, and production-oriented AI systems.

Perhaps the most valuable outcome was not the software itself, but the engineering mindset developed throughout the journey.

Understanding how to reason about systems, isolate problems, validate assumptions, and build incrementally is a transferable skill that applies to every future AI application.

The technologies used in this project will continue to evolve.

The engineering principles learned while building it are likely to remain valuable for many years.